The paper deals with distributed computing and algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of graphs and combinatorial structures suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible category. Finally, the mention of synchronous and asynchronous systems suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
